column5: Anyone hit scugog for bass lately,how did it go?
Sounds great ,was looking at launching from Island marina..good idea or no ?
Had a terrible evening last Friday. Had a 12" LMB hit 3 times and finally caught it. That was also it for the rest of the day. I'm sure scugog is always good for bass... well if you can find 'em!
Sounds like a persistant lil bugger. One is better than a skunk !
I run a Ranger with a 250 on the back.
Except for all those pesky locks! I may not be the sharpest in accounting but after looking at maps of ontario for years you become pretty good at geography! LOL
So i guess he just flies over them?
Yep,trouble is you cn only do it once so watch closely.
Best post in a while!  Could have been better, added "here hold my beer and watch this"
